{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Qne3pCaV5dTuUee5XP3YXa","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have all the information. Let me compile a comprehensive report.\n\n## Summary Report\n\nI've analyzed `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/db.ts` and found all the requested information. Here's what you need to know:\n\n### 1. **Db Interface** (Lines 238-485)\n\nThe `Db` interface defines methods for database operations organized into sections:\n\n**Key categories:**\n- **Rounds** (coinflip + jackpot): insertRound, deleteRoundByPda, updateRoundPhase, getRoundByPda, getRoundsByPhase, etc.\n- **Close Call rounds**: insertCloseCallRound, getCloseCallRound, settleCloseCallRound, etc.\n- **Transactions**: `insertTransaction`, `insertTransactions`, `getTransactions`\n- **Referral system**: insertReferralCode, getReferralCodeByWallet, insertReferralEarning, getReferralStats, etc.\n- **Player profiles**: createPlayerProfile, getProfileByWallet, updateUsername, **getPlayerStats**, **getPublicPlayerStats**\n- **Utility**: withTransaction (for DB transactions), close()\n\n### 2. **PlayerStats and PublicPlayerStats Types** (Lines 198-210)\n\n```typescript\nexport interface PlayerStats {\n  gamesPlayed: number;\n  totalWagered: bigint;\n  totalWins: number;\n  winRate: number;\n  netPnl: bigint;\n}\n\nexport interface PublicPlayerStats {\n  gamesPlayed: number;\n  totalWins: number;\n  winRate: number;\n}\n```\n\nNote: `PublicPlayerStats` omits `totalWagered` and `netPnl` for privacy.\n\n### 3. **getPlayerStats Implementation** (Lines 1135-1167)\n\nThe function uses a single SQL query on the `transactions` table with conditional aggregation:\n\n**SQL Pattern:**\n```sql\nSELECT\n  COUNT(DISTINCT CASE WHEN tx_type = 'deposit' THEN match_id END)::text AS games_played,\n  COALESCE(SUM(CASE WHEN tx_type = 'deposit' THEN amount_lamports ELSE 0 END), 0)::text AS total_wagered,\n  COUNT(DISTINCT CASE WHEN tx_type = 'payout' THEN match_id END)::text AS total_wins,\n  COALESCE(\n    SUM(CASE WHEN tx_type IN ('payout', 'refund') THEN amount_lamports\n             WHEN tx_type = 'deposit' THEN -amount_lamports\n             ELSE 0 END),\n    0\n  )::text AS net_pnl\nFROM transactions\nWHERE wallet = ${wallet}\n```\n\n**Logic:**\n- `gamesPlayed`: Count of distinct match_ids where tx_type='deposit' (wager entries)\n- `totalWagered`: Sum of amount_lamports where tx_type='deposit'\n- `totalWins`: Count of distinct match_ids where tx_type='payout'\n- `winRate`: Calculated as totalWins / gamesPlayed (or 0 if no games)\n- `netPnl`: Sum of (payouts + refunds as positive, deposits as negative) — net money made\n\n`getPublicPlayerStats` (lines 1169-1176) simply calls `getPlayerStats` and returns only the public fields.\n\n### 4. **Transactions Table Schema** (Migration 009, Lines 11-32)\n\nLocated at `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/migrations/009_transactions.sql`:\n\n**Columns:**\n- `id` — BIGSERIAL PRIMARY KEY\n- `wallet` — TEXT (NOT NULL) — player's wallet address\n- `game` — TEXT (NOT NULL) — game type/name\n- `match_id` — TEXT (NOT NULL) — round/match identifier\n- `tx_type` — TEXT (NOT NULL) — one of 'deposit', 'payout', 'refund'\n- `amount_lamports` — BIGINT (NOT NULL) — SOL amount in lamports\n- `tx_sig` — TEXT (NOT NULL) — on-chain transaction signature\n- `created_at` — TIMESTAMPTZ (DEFAULT now())\n\n**Indexes:**\n- `idx_tx_wallet_created` on (wallet, created_at DESC) for paginated history\n- `idx_tx_match_id` on (match_id) for match lookup\n- `uq_tx_wallet_match_type_sig` UNIQUE on (wallet, match_id, tx_type, tx_sig) for idempotency\n\n### 5. **insertTransaction Implementation** (Lines 784-813)\n\n**Single insert** (lines 784-797):\n```typescript\nasync insertTransaction(params) {\n  await sql`\n    INSERT INTO transactions (wallet, game, match_id, tx_type, amount_lamports, tx_sig)\n    VALUES (...)\n    ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING\n  `;\n}\n```\n\n**Batch insert** (lines 799-813):\nUses `sql()` helper to build a multi-row insert with ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING.\n\n**Key pattern:** ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING ensures idempotency—duplicate (wallet, match_id, tx_type, tx_sig) tuples are silently ignored.\n\nAll amounts are in **lamports** (u64 as BIGINT in PostgreSQL). The InsertTransactionParams type (lines 118-125) matches the columns exactly."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0ca033a0-a8fc-41b6-94ce-75284f4db80b","uuid":"7f2d66ed-098c-4423-88b2-50ac5c915c52","timestamp":"2026-03-31T15:05:35.490Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to understand the structure of `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/db.ts` — specifically:\n1. The `Db` interface (what methods are on it)\n2. The `getPlayerStats` function implementation (what SQL patterns it uses, what table/columns it queries)\n3. The `PlayerStats` and `PublicPlayerStats` types\n4. The `transactions` table columns (look at how they're queried)\n5. The `insertUserTransaction` function to understand the table schema\n\nRead the file carefully. It may be large. Focus on the stats-related code and the Db interface definition. Report the relevant code sections with line numbers.","agentId":"a506bd2b804d6729e","agentType":"Explore","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have all the information. Let me compile a comprehensive report.\n\n## Summary Report\n\nI've analyzed `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/db.ts` and found all the requested information. Here's what you need to know:\n\n### 1. **Db Interface** (Lines 238-485)\n\nThe `Db` interface defines methods for database operations organized into sections:\n\n**Key categories:**\n- **Rounds** (coinflip + jackpot): insertRound, deleteRoundByPda, updateRoundPhase, getRoundByPda, getRoundsByPhase, etc.\n- **Close Call rounds**: insertCloseCallRound, getCloseCallRound, settleCloseCallRound, etc.\n- **Transactions**: `insertTransaction`, `insertTransaction